  "quality": "research",
  "notes": "Mirandese (mirandés), spoken in the Miranda do Douro municipality, northeastern Portugal. Classified as Asturleonese. Recognised as a regional/minority language in Portugal since 1999. Retains archaic Asturleonese features: diphthongisation of Latin short /e/ and /o/, palatal lateral /ʎ/ preserved, nasal vowels influenced by Portuguese orthographic proximity. Heavy Portuguese adstrate via official education and administration.",
